goals.question: What is the distribution of obesity rates across states?

goals.rationale: This visualization will help identify states with high and low obesity rates and any regional patterns.

goals.rationale: This visualization will help identify any regional differences in obesity rates.

goals.question: What is the relationship between obesity rates and state population?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of obesity rate vs state population
goals.rationale: This visualization will help identify any correlation between obesity rates and state population.

goals.question: What is the distribution of obesity rates within each region?
goals.visualization: box plot of obesity rates by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help identify any regional differences in the distribution of obesity rates.

goals.question: What is the most common obesity rate range across all states?

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import geopandas as gpd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    us_states = gpd.read_file('https://raw.githubusercontent.com/PublicaMundi/MappingAPI/master/data/geojson/us-states.json')
    us_states = us_states.merge(data, left_on='name', right_on='state')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,10))
    us_states.plot(column='rate', cmap='OrRd', linewidth=0.8, ax=ax, edgecolor='0.8')
    ax.axis('off')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of obesity rates across states?', fontdict={'fontsize': '25', 'fontweight' : '3'})
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region')['rate'].mean().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['region'], data['rate'])
    plt.title('What is the average obesity rate by region?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.scatter(data['rate'], data['id'], alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Obesity Rate')
    ax.set_ylabel('State Population')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between obesity rates and state population?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 7))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['region'] == 'A']['rate'], data[data['region'] == 'B']['rate'], data[data['region'] == 'C']['rate'], data[data['region'] == 'D']['rate'], data[data['region'] == 'E']['rate'], data[data['region'] == 'F']['rate'], data[data['region'] == 'G']['rate'], data[data['region'] == 'H']['rate'], data[data['region'] == 'I']['rate']])
    ax.set_xticklabels(['A', 'B', 'C', 'D', 'E', 'F', 'G', 'H', 'I'])
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Obesity Rate')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of obesity rates within each region?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['rate'].plot(kind='hist', bins=10, color='purple', edgecolor='black', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['rate'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label='Mean')
    plt.title('What is the most common obesity rate range across all states?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
